Patch Set 5: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Looking at how the existing metadata encryption works, I don't think this patch is heading in the right direction.

The existing metadata encryption consists of two parts. For v1, all encryption and decryption takes place in the registry client. For v2, there is a little adapter step in the domain logic for the database code that decrypts on the way out of the db and encrypts on the way in.

I think we need to keep that model, if just for the sake of avoiding spreading these details all across the codebase.

Patch Set 5:

Hi markwash, let me answer you questions and explain what I did here.


1. Correct thare are two parts contain encryption and decryption handing for glance-registry v1 and v2 api separately, and v2 part is in the domain at https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/db/__init__.py#L99 and L128 and that's ok. This bug/patch just for v1 part only but v2, so I'm not breaking existing model.


2. Actually on glance-registry v1 server side we also need encryption and decryption handing since when in glance-api v1 controller, image object has 'location' and 'location_data' two fields (keep Forward-compatible, jbresnahan's multi-location patch did), so when we want to save image's locations back to db in glance-registry v1 controller we need combine them back to 'locations' field (https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/registry/api/v1/images.py#L55). So without my this fixes, the combination handling will be failed since the location url string is different even they are same actually, and location db record will be duplicated, and image locations field will be wrong also when glance load it back on next time.

Thanks.
Uploaded patch set 6.
